content.text:
Here's an improved version of your CSS with better defaults, responsive design, and modern best practices:

```css
/* CSS Custom Properties for consistency */
:root {
  --max-width: 1200px;
  --spacing-unit: 1rem;
  --color-text: #333;
  --color-bg: #fff;
  --font-family-base: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
  --font-size-base: 16px;
  --line-height-base: 1.5;
}

/* Reset and base styles */
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

html {
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
}

body {
  font-family: var(--font-family-base);
  font-size: var(--font-size-base);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);
  color: var(--color-text);
  background-color: var(--color-bg);
}

/* Responsive container */
.container {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: var(--max-width);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 var(--spacing-unit);
}

/* Optional: Responsive padding for larger screens */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    padding: 0 calc(var(--spacing-unit) * 2);
  }
}

/* Typography improvements */
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  line-height: 1.2;
  margin-bottom: 0.5em;
}

p {
  margin-bottom: 1em;
}

/* Link improvements */
a {
  color: inherit;
  text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

/* Image responsiveness */
img {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
}
```

**Key improvements:**

1. **CSS Variables**: Makes it easy to maintain consistent spacing, colors, and fonts
2. **Complete Reset**: Universal selector (`*`) with `box-sizing: border-box` for predictable sizing
3. **Better Typography**: Proper font stack, line height, and heading defaults
4. **Centered Container**: Added `margin: 0 auto` to properly center the container
5. **Responsive Padding**: Container has horizontal padding that increases on larger screens
6. **Accessibility**: Smooth scroll behavior, better line heights, readable color contrast
7. **Image Optimization**: Ensures images scale responsively
8. **Link Styling**: Basic hover states and proper color inheritance

Would you like me to adjust any specific parts, add more features (like dark mode, animations, or additional components)?

